OL,3,CShop staff 'facing Christmas crime
OL,4,Cwave' with more shoplifting cases
OL,5,Cunsolved
OL,7,FThis is a 38% increase from the total
OL,8,Fnumber of shoplifting offences that
OL,9,Fwent unsolved in the same period five
OL,10,Fyears ago.
OL,12,FMore than half (56.4%) of shoplifting
OL,13,Fcases were closed because no suspect
OL,14,Fwas identified, and only around one in
OL,15,Fsix cases resulted in someone being
OL,16,Fcharged or summonsed in the past year.
